&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Tahoma;" lang="EN-GB"&gt;Decomposition
of ammonium nitrate in NP buffer tank due to high temperature and low pH in the
tank. This caused huge gas formation and rupture of the tank due to
overpressure. The overheating was a result of a leaking steam valve on the 20
bar steam supply to the tank.&amp;nbsp; The indirect causes were that no hazards
for the NP buffer tank were defined in the Hazop study or the risk analysis and
that the tank was not equipped with any automatic safety functions, only
alarms. It is also concluded that there&amp;nbsp;was insufficient follow up of the
plant at shut down conditions.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

